  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Introduction:

      Different groups already showed in retrospective subgroup analyses, that there is an
      increased risk for cardiovascular events in patients on a simultaneous ASA/NSAID treatment.

      Methods:

      Light-Transmission aggregometry

      Hypothesis:

      Simultaneous administration of different NSAIDs and ASA impair the platelet inhibiting effect
      of ASA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
